Of the 223 funds in the Asisa (Association for Savings and Investment SA) South Africa equity general sector, 121 recorded net outflows for the year the end of February, according to Morningstar. That is 54% of the sector. Notably, two of the three largest funds in this category saw net outflows of more than R1 billion over this period. Subscribe for full access to all our share and unit trust data tools, our award-winning articles, and support quality journalism in the process. You will be redirected to a checkout page.
